      "response": "Much of the surplus is likely to be needed for our debt service, and we do need to examine doing more pay-go with our capital projects so as not to be carrying so much debt. That said, I would like us to fully fund Homeward DC, the District strategic plan to end homelessness, as well as additional funding to our Local Rent Supplement Program, the Housing Production Trust Fund, and maintenance funds for our public housing stock.     I was one of the few Councilmembers who did not support the roll back of the District's estate tax last year, which will benefit a very small number of residents, and instead offered an amendment to the budget. Unfortunately that amendment failed. I believe we have too many problems  especially affordability and homelessness  and the funding we lost should have been used to address these issues where it could have helped thousands.     Should we find ourselves in a recession, or even with budget shortfalls due to rollbacks of the Affordable Care Act and Medicaid, we should strongly consider increasing taxes on our wealthiest residents, including an end to the current rollback of the estate tax. With a shortfall that large, we cannot rely on our rainy day fund and otherwise would have to begin cutting services to our residents.  "
